element.name: Hole In The Wall by AbbeyAckbar, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)
element.description:
The cache is located at the Hole in the wall beach (Burrow beach). We recommend you gain entry to the beach via Claremont road. Parking is available on this road. Alternatively, you could take the Dart to Sutton train station or get the 31, 31B or 31C bus which serve Sutton and walk to the cache from there. Please enjoy a walk along the beach, but:
BE WARY OF TIDAL CHANNELS AROUND LOW WATER.
element.long-description:
Burrow beach is a wonderful sandy beach with scenic views. It is a continuation of Claremont beach. It's known as The Hole In The Wall as that's how people gained access to the beach from Claremont Road. The old wall is gone, but the little lane reamains between the houses.
Initial Cache Contents: FTF Prize : Magnetic Travel Ludo Game & FTF Badge!
Ladybird peg
Wooden Clown Whistle
Lavender Candle
Ping Pong Ball
Golf Tee
Beyblades Badge
Purple Lizard
Magic Roundabout Spinner
Geocaching Badge
Wooden Spin Top
Joker Playing Card
Toy Plane
Cat Keyring
FAS LED Keyring
Red Furry Pencil
Purple Hippo Face Window Sucker

Our first find outside the US!!! This one was near our hotel and afforded us an enjoyable and scenic walk on the beach. Very creative cache!! TFTC

2010-06-07T19:00:00Z : Found it by irishfoxes
Lovely beach. Nice size cache with lots in it.

2010-05-15T19:00:00Z : Found it by Nosugrefs
Great camo, Nice walk along the beach, although a little on the cold side for those from down under.

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Toffee Man
First find of the day in the Howth area on a lovely sunny day. TFTC Toffee Man #334

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Write note by Fitzet
This is the biggest and busiest cache around so made a quick trip this evening to drop off a number of travel bugs. They shouldn't have to wait long to move on.
In : Good luck to you fellow cacher TB, Photo Travel Bug TB, TC's Roots Crawler TB, U2 Around the World TB (Cache is close to Larry's house...) Out: Nothing

2008-11-09T20:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Our first for the day and Gavin and Anton's first ever. We walked up from Sutton and initially went right past the easy access - until we saw someone confirming that although closed to cars it was possible for us to go that very handy way.
Great cache, I'd be inclined to call it a large instead of a regular myself. Took a coin and left a coin.
